Earlier this week, our Director of Research, Dr. Justin Perrault, and Research Technician, Karen Lohman, went sampling in Crystal River for a project looking at the presence of fibropapillomatosis and health and immune system effects of this disease in sea turtles. This project will help us better understand the health and immune system effects of the disease, which until this point has been relatively understudied in Florida. Thank you to @inwaterresearch for helping acquire funding for the project and overseeing sample collections.
